I've debated with myself about making this post over and over, so here it goes... when I first started blowing glass (November 7th 2017) it was simply bc my friend had a torch and kept asking me to try and make something (I was a diver doing boat salvation & underwater construction prior to making glass full time) I knew nothing about the glass scene whatsoever. Finally, I tried my hand at it, and I literally became obsessed. I started searching different artists on here for inspiration and found Mike Gong (original gongster) page. I saw his acid eaters, and I genuinely thought they were the coolest thing on earth. So I then became fully dedicated to becoming as good as the artists I was inspired by & looked up to, Mike being by far my biggest inspiration. I learned this technique by spending hours & hours every day trying to figure it out. After about a year of non-stop trial & error, countless failures, I finally started to achieve what I set out to do, make something similar. It was never about making money, I would have laughed if you told me I was going to make a living off of it at the time. It was simply because I wanted one so bad, but there was no way I could spend 3k+ on a pendant. Word got out that I was progressing with them, and my name got out there because of that. Fast forward another year, and of course, I had a lot of people hitting me up wanting one & as a new glass artist that wanted nothing more than to make it my life/living I started selling them. I got a lot of love and a lot of hate as well. I spoke with Mike through dm. He at the time said how impressed he was that I was able to figure it out the way I did.  Every post I made, I gave credit that I was inspired by Gong. He ended up blocking me about a month after we spoke and has me blocked to this day. I was told I'd never make it in the glass industry, that I'd never be anything but a biter, and my only success was by "copying" being inspired by Mike. Even though I could still be making money on these and genuinely enjoy making them, I stopped and found my own style to prove all the haters wrong. So that's exactly what I did. TBC in the comment section bc I've reached my caption limit.

It's a long story how it came about (IYKYK)🤷‍♂️🤣.... However, I made my first shark tooth (mako shark) almost exactly 1 month ago, June 8th. Kinda weird that it's taken me so long to attempt one bc I've been obsessed with sharks since I was little. I ended up gifting this one to the homie @gstring69_  during my meet & greet at the @grassrootscalifornia booth at @electric_forest.. Anyway, I'm trying to judge interest in these. If there is enough interest. I will do a limited batch of 50 max, then no more.. As I grow as an artist & understand what art truly means/should mean. I've come to realize that my pieces become way more cherished as well as desirable when I only do limited amounts of each design. Such as my Dino & gator skulls. That being said, you can expect to see my tree pendants stick around as that's truly my favorite style I've taught myself to make. Please leave a comment if you'd be interested in a shark tooth from me. As always, thanks for looking! ☺️🙏💜
